So do you ever have those days where you clip a part off the sprue and it shoots across the room never to be found again? It's Easy enough to do.

So for anyone else who lost Part #A15 of the AT18 Warhound Plastic Kit I give you a resin printer friendly replacement made with a cut out polygon and some resized 40k scale exhausts. I left the base plate slightly thick so you don't have any issues with the whole thing splintering apart while taking it off the supports.

Printed out fine on my Photon.

An AT18 Rescale and Remix of Jimbeamz Lucius Wardog. I removed some iconography and modded a couple of bits plus merged some and added pre-done holes in the torso. Its not perfect but it should work and is fairly close in height to one of the official plastic Mars Pattern Kits. Please note I have not done the Plasma or Flamer weapons yet. I will upload them when they are done.

Notes:
- Primarily aimed at being printed on a DLP Printer
- Parts are not merged so if you want to repose the legs feel free.
- If GW release a plastic version of this I will be removing it. At the moment it is an unavailable kit so I'm posting this in good faith for free.
- Do not request re-ups of the original 40k Scale file. I won't be doing that.


Edit 05/02/2020: Added remixed Turbo Plasma and the Plasma Canisters for it.

Edit 06/02/2020: Found Three Rivets I missed removing that floated in space under the Turbo Plasma, added a fixed version of the file. If you downloaded on day one grab the new file.

Edit 08/02/2020: Noticed some weird artifacting in the plasma gun when you slice it. Specifically there appears to be an invisible block extending in the core of the weapon into the socket for the arm mount. I'll have to work out which addition is causing this and clean it up manually. If you print it out before then you will need to dremel or drill out the socket. I'll try and fix this when i get some time off work.

Re-scale and remix of Jimzbeanz Power Fist to suit the 2018 Version of Adeptus Titanicus, with Upper Arm components rescaled from Strogs 40k Version. Added the magnet well so it can easily be used with the Plastic kits. Designed to print on DLP printers.

EDIT 12/01/2020 - I went to print this today and noticed I hadn't seated the mounting ring for the magnet correctly in the upper arm. Uploaded the fixed Version 2 file.

EDIT 19/01/2020 - I did a test print and the fist itself is a bit too large when compared to an AT18 Warlord Titan. I will work on the re-scaling and test this probably tomorrow since i have the day off. It is for now perfectly scaled to suit 28mm Knights, which is kind of cool/funny.

EDIT 17/03/2020 - So after some feedback the following files itself need to be scaled to 80% - Palm_WithFingers, Thumb_Complete and Palm_Gun. The Elbow_Joint needs to be scaled to 90%. This will give a much closer scaling to the Plastic version and won't look as oversized.

Go nuts, rescale it and print one for your 40K scale minis. Swap the barrels out for gargoyle heads and put it on Chaos stuff. Make Giant Battle Crabs by remixing it (ok so I am doing one or two of those myself, you got me!)
How you use it is up to you!

I can't tell you what to do, I'm not your Mom :P

Serious Note: The this was a personal fun project rather than ordering one from the overprices resin dealers at FW. Yes it would have been cheaper to just buy one.
If you want to rescale it for a 40k Warlord you might need to add extra detail, dunno I made it busy enough for AT.
